\startsection{Class}{xDesktop}{l12}{%

\label{l318}\label{l319}}%end signature
\begin{itemize}
\sld
\item{
\sld
{\bf Usage}
  \begin{itemize}\isep
   \item{
Get list of services from DIM name server defined by DIM\_DNS\_NODE, filtered by wildcard.
 Commands and parameters are kept in separate lists and ordered alphabetically.
 Names not matching the DABC format (four elements separated by slashes) are handled separately. 
 Only DIM EXIT commands are formatted according DABC,
 but in xDimCommand they are restored for execution. This might need better solution.
}%end item
  \end{itemize}
}

{\bf Parameters}

\membername{infoHandler}
{\tt public void {\bf infoHandler}(  )
\label{l352}\label{l353}}%end signature
\begin{itemize}
\sld
\item{
\sld
{\bf Usage}
  \begin{itemize}\isep
   \item{
The DIM parameter DIS\_DNS$/$SERVER\_LIST is either a list, or incremental.
 That means it may start with + to add a server, or with - to remove a server,
 or a list of servers separated by |:\mbox{}\newline

 +name@node -name@node name@node|name@node|name@node\mbox{}\newline

 This handler only handles the increments. On startup the text area is
 filled with the server list by xBrowser.getServers function.
}%end item
  \end{itemize}
}

\startsection{Class}{xDimParameter}{l16}{%
{\small A list of these objects is the central management of DIM parameters.
 It implements the DIM handler, creates the graphical elements, the records keeping
 parameter values, and interface functions to access these values.
 It also has reference to table model. On parameter update, the table and all graphical objects are updated.}
\vskip .1in 
\startsubsubsection{Declaration}{
\fbox{\vbox{
\hbox{\vbox{\small public 
class 
xDimParameter}}
\noindent\hbox{\vbox{{\bf extends} dim.DimInfo}}
\noindent\hbox{\vbox{{\bf implements} 
xiDimParameter}}
}}}

{\tt int } {\bf col} )
\label{l860}\label{l861}}%end signature
\begin{itemize}
\sld
\item{
\sld
{\bf Usage}
  \begin{itemize}\isep
   \item{
Uses JPanel with GridBagLayout. Assumes that all items have same size.
 Items are ordered in lines, each line has same number of columns (except last one).
 Number of columns define number of lines.
}%end item
  \end{itemize}
}

  \end{itemize}
}%end item

\startsection{Class}{xPanelParameter}{l37}{%
{\small Handles parameter table. On parameter update, the table is updated.}
\vskip .1in 
\startsubsubsection{Declaration}{
\fbox{\vbox{
\hbox{\vbox{\small public 
class 
xPanelParameter}}
\noindent\hbox{\vbox{{\bf extends} javax.swing.JPanel}}
\noindent\hbox{\vbox{{\bf implements} 
javax.swing.event.TableModelListener}}
}}}
\startsubsubsection{Serializable Fields}{
}
\startsubsubsection{Constructors}{
\vskip -2em
\begin{itemize}
\item{\vskip -1.9ex 
\membername{xPanelParameter}
{\tt public {\bf xPanelParameter}( {\tt xgui.xDimBrowser } {\bf browser},
{\tt java.awt.Dimension } {\bf dim} )
\label{l944}\label{l945}}%end signature
\begin{itemize}
\sld
\item{
\sld
{\bf Usage}
  \begin{itemize}\isep
   \item{
Panel for parameter table. Gets xDimParameter list from browser and calls initPanel.
 Polls over all parameters until all have been updated at least once (quality valid).
 Cleans all graphics panels and build new table.
 Graphics panels must be rebuilt from caller.
 Keeps a list of command descriptors (xXmlParser).
}%end item
  \end{itemize}
}
\item{
\sld
{\bf Parameters}
\sld\isep
  \begin{itemize}
\sld\isep
   \item{
\sld
{\tt browser} - DIM browser.}
   \item{
\sld
{\tt dim} - Size and position of window.}
  \end{itemize}
}%end item
\end{itemize}
}%end item
\end{itemize}
}

\startsection{Class}{xParser}{l42}{%
{\small Parser for (de)composing DIM service names.
 The DIM service names of DABC follow a defined structure,
 mainly Dns$/$Node[:NodeId]$/$[applNS::]Application[:ApplicationId]$/$Name.}
\vskip .1in

}}}

\item{\vskip -1.9ex 
\membername{format}
{\tt public int {\bf format}(  )
\label{l1034}\label{l1035}}%end signature
\begin{itemize}
\sld
\item{
\sld
{\bf Usage}
  \begin{itemize}\isep
   \item{
parse internal DIM format string set by setFormat(string).
 The items of the string are copied into internal string arrays and can be retreived by getter methods.  \bl 
 DIM format strings have format \bl  \textless 
 T:S;T:S;...\textgreater  \bl 
 For scalar data set default size to 1 (eventually this should be 0?);
 for structures, the last item size defaults to 0 indicating that it has arbitrary size
}%end item
  \end{itemize}
}
\item{{\bf Returns} - 
0 OK,  -1 syntax error 
}%end item
\end{itemize}
}%end item
